<br>
The hybrid XP penalty was bad, they finally relented on that.  Rogues were useless pre-Kunark, they fixed that.  They fixed it a bit too well, IMO, but they fixed it.  There was never a reason to be a warrior back when SKs and Pallys tanked just as well, they fixed that.  Again, a bit too large a swing in favor of warriors, IMO, but they did listen.  Wizards were useless in Velious raids, they listened and gave us banes.  A bad solution, but on this one case, we got the long end of the stick.  They listened when we complained about the Cazic skin drops on our epic, they listened when rangers were getting pasted in Kunark and gave rangers jolt, they (finally) got beaten enough on the monk feign and fixed it, and it works wonderfully now.  They listened when druids complained about healing ability post 50 and upgraded them.  Again, not enough, because they do not realize the power of CHeal, but at least they tried.  They gave us the staff of the wheel quest when Ice Comet was impossible to get.  And now they are trying to balance melee damage because SKs and pallys are getting hozed by warriors and monks are getting hozed by rogues.  And I do think they are going to look at melee v caster damage soon and, if not actually fix, at least try to fix, that imbalance.<br>
<br>
These are just a few examples.  There are more.  The class specific armor quests in place of the horrific rubicite camps.  They may not always get it right, and they have proven time and time again that simple math is beyond them, but Verant does listen and Verant does try.  The game now is very different from the game on release, in part due to player complaints and Verant response, be that response good or bad.<br>
<br>
Verant can't really be at the beck and call of the loudest web posters, honestly.  Some people never will be satisfied (a lot of these people play necros).  Some people want their pet class to be god like.  Some suggestions are dumb and should be ignored, some people should be ignored.<br>
<br>
Verant has issues.  Their customer service borders on fascist.  From the outside, I imagine their code is a spaghetti tangled mess.  Simple math eludes them, and some egos over there seem to be out of control.  But to say they are all bad short changes them, I think. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaphasiaandesite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aphasia Andesite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/30/01 11:05:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Verant really does not care what you think, here is why.</span><hr size=1> wow nice post burrow, easy to forget all that stuff. Hopefully they get to us sooner than later.<br>
